question_title: Will OpenAI release a model named 'GPT-6' for general public availability before May 1, 2026?
summary: GPT-6 release before May 1, 2026 is very unlikely. OpenAI officially confirmed GPT-6 would not ship in 2025, and as of late January 2026 they are still iterating on the GPT-5 series (GPT-5.2 released December 2025). Sam Altman said the wait for GPT-6 would be shorter than GPT-4→GPT-5 (~2 years), suggesting earliest mid-2026 at best. Hardware for next-gen models arrives H2 2026. There is no official announcement, leaked date, or credible indication of an imminent GPT-6 launch. The Manifold market for "GPT-6 before June 1, 2026" is at ~17%, and our deadline is a month earlier. The question resolves in ~3 months with no sign of an approaching release.

factors.description: OpenAI officially confirmed GPT-6 not shipping in 2025; still iterating on GPT-5 series (5.2 released Dec 2025, updated Jan 2026)
No official announcement, leaked release date, or credible indication of imminent GPT-6 launch as of Jan 2026
Hardware for next-gen models (compute needed for GPT-6) arriving H2 2026; Altman cited compute constraints
Only ~3 months until May 1 deadline - extremely short window for a major model launch with no signals
Manifold market for 'GPT-6 before June 1 2026' at 16.6%; our deadline is a month earlier, implying even lower probability
Sam Altman said GPT-6 gap will be shorter than GPT-4→5 (~2 years), and OpenAI is accelerating development
Speculative sources mention 'early 2026' as possible window, but no credible confirmation
